From: Tomoatsu Shimada <shimada@walbrix.com>
Subject: [PATCH] debug: Add 'no-damage-detection' flag to disable GPU damage
 detection

Add a new GNOME_REMOTE_DESKTOP_DEBUG flag 'no-damage-detection' that
bypasses the GPU compute shader damage detection pipeline and forces
every frame to be re-encoded in full (equivalent to the 'simple' path
that is used for the first frame of each session).

Normally, from the second frame onward, grd submits a Vulkan compute
shader that compares the new and old source images block-by-block and
only marks changed 16x16 blocks as dirty.  On some GPU/driver
combinations (observed on Intel Arc B580 / BMG / Xe2 with Mesa anv,
and also on Celeron N4020 / Gemini Lake / ANV) the damage detection
produces false "unchanged" results, causing stale block content to
remain visible on the client side.

With 'no-damage-detection' set, every block is always marked dirty so
the encoder re-encodes the full frame each time.  This trades higher
bandwidth and slightly higher GPU load for visually correct output.

Typical use:

  GNOME_REMOTE_DESKTOP_DEBUG=no-damage-detection

Or in combination with other flags:

  GNOME_REMOTE_DESKTOP_DEBUG=no-damage-detection,no-avc444

The flag leaves the AVC444 dual-stream path and the VAAPI encoder path
unaffected; only the compute-shader step that feeds the encoder input
is changed.

---
 src/grd-debug.c              | 1 +
 src/grd-debug.h              | 1 +
 src/grd-rdp-view-creator-avc.c | 3 ++-
 3 files changed, 4 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/grd-debug.c b/src/grd-debug.c
index e9478e8..5cb24d9 100644
--- a/src/grd-debug.c
+++ b/src/grd-debug.c
@@ -32,6 +32,7 @@ static const GDebugKey grd_debug_keys[] = {
   { "va-times", GRD_DEBUG_VA_TIMES },
   { "vkva-renderer", GRD_DEBUG_VKVA },
   { "no-avc444", GRD_DEBUG_NO_AVC444 },
+  { "no-damage-detection", GRD_DEBUG_NO_DAMAGE_DETECTION },
 };

 static GrdDebugFlags debug_flags;
diff --git a/src/grd-debug.h b/src/grd-debug.h
index 2b7a6ac..8b6237c 100644
--- a/src/grd-debug.h
+++ b/src/grd-debug.h
@@ -30,6 +30,7 @@ typedef enum _GrdDebugFlags
   GRD_DEBUG_VA_TIMES = 1 << 4,
   GRD_DEBUG_VKVA = 1 << 5,
   GRD_DEBUG_NO_AVC444 = 1 << 6,
+  GRD_DEBUG_NO_DAMAGE_DETECTION = 1 << 7,
 } GrdDebugFlags;

 GrdDebugFlags grd_get_debug_flags (void);
diff --git a/src/grd-rdp-view-creator-avc.c b/src/grd-rdp-view-creator-avc.c
index 870e647..34fe970 100644
--- a/src/grd-rdp-view-creator-avc.c
+++ b/src/grd-rdp-view-creator-avc.c
@@ -528,7 +528,8 @@ grd_rdp_view_creator_avc_create_view (GrdRdpViewCreator  *view_creator,
     command_buffers->init_state_buffers;
   ++n_buffer_submit_infos;

-  if (src_image_old)
+  if (src_image_old &&
+      !(grd_get_debug_flags () & GRD_DEBUG_NO_DAMAGE_DETECTION))
     create_dual_view = command_buffers->create_dual_view_difference;
   else
     create_dual_view = command_buffers->create_dual_view_simple;
